## Checklist

Before reporting completion:

- [ ] Accepted task context from execution prompt
- [ ] Followed TDD cycle (tests first, watched fail, implemented, refactored)
- [ ] **Inner loop passing after each cycle** (test + lint + typecheck)
- [ ] All tests passing (no failures, no skipped)
- [ ] Lint and format checks passing
- [ ] Build successful
- [ ] **All acceptance criteria verified** (from ticket)
- [ ] **Frontend: verified in browser** (if UI changes)
- [ ] Code review requested and passed
- [ ] Review feedback applied
- [ ] Committed with conventional commit message
- [ ] Run final verification in affected module: `just lint format test`
- [ ] **Emitted completion signal:** `<completion>TASK:{phase_id}:{task_index}:STATUS</completion>`
- [ ] Completion summary provided

## Remember

- **TDD is mandatory** - no implementation before tests
- **Inner loop after every cycle** - test, lint, typecheck before moving on
- **Code review is mandatory** - no completion without review approval
- **All checks must pass** - tests, lint, format, build
- **Work autonomously** - proceed without confirmation, stop only when truly blocked
- **Incorporate CI feedback** - fix failures without waiting for instruction
- **Report back clearly** - execution needs summary to track progress
- **Handle errors gracefully** - retry or report, don't fail silently
